----------

In the context of the project DECADE (D=C3=A9couverte et exploitation des
connaissances pour l'aide =C3=A0 la d=C3=A9cision en chimie th=C3=A9rapeuti=
que), the CoDaG
research group of the GREYC laboratory at the university of Caen, France,
offers a research internship for 2nd-year master students (or equivalent).

* Context *

High-throughput screening has become an indispensible component for finding
promising molecules (i.e. molecules that show activity for certain targets)
that can be further developed into drugs. Unfortunately, the screening also
flags so-called promiscuous molecules, the "PAINS" (Pan Assay Interference
Compounds), which do not lead to drug development because they often exhibi=
t a
toxic effects. The identification of a PAINS in silico is difficult, and,
additionally, scientific articles occassionally describe molecules as
promising that actually turn out to be PAINS. From the point of view of
computational chemistry, the project DECADE aims at identifying new PAINS.

* Topic *

Even if the use of data mining approaches for the identification and
characterization of PAINS is theoretically rather well understood, the
practical application adds additional bottle necks and challenges. In the
context of this internship, the applicability of existing techniques will be
explored, as well as the development of an interface to direct the mining
process. The internship comprises four sub-tasks: 1) evaluate if text mining
tools can be used to recover PAINS that have already been identified in the
literature, 2) use unsupervised (or semi-supervised) techniques to group
similar molecules and verify the quality of found clusters, e.g. regarding =
the
grouping of PAINS and non-PAINS, 3) mine discriminating substructures and
assess their biological meaning in interaction with experts in medical
chemistry, 4) implement an interface allowing to express different constrai=
nts
and to automatically acquire additional data and/or filter data already
acquired.

* Profil *

The candidate should have knowledge in data mining, ideally in text mining,
graph mining, or semi-supervised (constrained) clustering. Programming skil=
ls
are required.

Duration: 3 months

* Contact *

To apply, please send your CV to albrecht.zimmermann@unicaen.fr
